ms to admire France’s aristocratic cultural heritage. Drawing on archival evidence from across the country, the book presents a compelling account of power, interest and emotion in family dynamics and nobles’ relations with rural and urban communities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCultural propertyzFrancexHistoryyModern period, 1500-. 0aCultural propertyzFrance. 0aNobilityzFrancexHistoryyModern period, 1500-. 0aNobilityzFrancexHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aFrance.  afamily.  aheritage.  amemory.  anobility.1 aMacknight, Elizabeth C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612052640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526120526423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526120526/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles